# Assassins Crew

"Killers for hire" (p. 99). Our crew: [[The Creed]].

## XP trigger

Earn xp when you execute a successful **accident, disappearance, murder, or ransom** operation (p. 99).

## Favored operation types (p. 100)

- **Accident** — a killing with no telltale signs of murder
- **Disappearance** — the victim vanishes without a trace
- **Murder** — an obvious killing that sends a message ← The Creed's focus
- **Ransom** — kidnapping and demand for payment

## Starting upgrades

Training: Prowess (p. 100). Note Assassins' base Training from the sheet also lists Insight.

## Crew upgrades (p. 100)

- **Assassin Rigging** — 2 free load of weapon or gear items
- **Ironhook Contacts** — effective Tier +1 in prison, incl. incarceration rolls (see [[Ironhook Prison]])
- **Elite Skulks** — +1d to quality rolls for Skulk cohort actions

## Contacts (p. 100)

Trev (gang boss), Lydra (deal broker), Irimina (vicious noble), Karlos (bounty hunter), Exeter (Spirit Warden), Sevoy (merchant lord)

## Setting warning

Death draws the spirit bells and vengeful ghosts in Duskwall — "Be prepared!" (p. 99)
